President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Washington due to severe winter storms, straight-line winds, flooding, landslides, mudslides, and a tornado that occurred from December 10 to December 24, 2018. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. The funding will be available on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Dolph A. Diemont has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further damage assessments may lead to additional designations in the future. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.